{
  "text": "All transfected Rsk1 constructs used in these studies were derived from the avian Rsk1 cDNA, and were detected using avian-specific Rsk1 antibodies. Avian Rsk1 shares greater than 80% identity with murine, human and Xenopus Rsk1 and they are regulated in a similar fashion [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . GST-GSK3β was generated by placing Met1-Ala22 of human GSK3β (a gift of B. Neel) into pGEX-3X (Pharmacia). GST-S6 contains Lys218-Lys249 of Rat S6 in pGEX-3X (Pharmacia). GST-Bad was generated by placing full-length murine Bad (from pEBG-Bad, NEB) into pGEX-4T-1 (Pharmacia). Point mutants of Bad (S112A, S136A and S112A,S136A) were generated using the quickchange approach (Stratagene). Generation of an activated allele of Rsk1 was done by cloning either the avian [CITATION_5] or human Rsk1 cDNA downstream of a DNA linker encoding six amino acids (MGSSKS) of the Src myristoylation signal in pCMV6 (a gift of P. Tsichlis). Plasmids pCMV6-HA-Akt and pCMV6-Myr-Akt-HA were gifts of P. Tsichlis. HA-Rsk1 and HA-Rsk1∆∆ (K112R/K464R) were generated by placing avian Rsk1 wild-type and mutant cDNAs into pKH [CITATION_6] . Plasmid pRK7-Mek-DD was a gift from R. Erikson. pCMV-GFP-PH encodes the pleckstrin homology domain of spectrin fused to GFP (gift of R.F. Kalejta, T. Shenk and A.J. Beavis). For cotransfection experiments, Rsk1 constructs were cloned into pMT2, which is driven by an SV40 promoter and allowed for efficient production of the cotransfected protein(s).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "682778",
